HEADWORD: Pyrognostics
<hw>Pyr`og*nos"tics</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos>
<fld>(Min.)</fld> <def>The characters of a mineral observed by the use
of the blowpipe, as the degree of fusibility, flame coloration,
etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

